<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="recipe-page">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4 recipe-image">
      <img src="/images/logo-2.jpeg" alt="recipe image" class="img-fluid" />
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-8 recipe-description">
      <h1>
        <strong>Grilled Lemon-Pepper Chicken</strong>
      </h1>
      <p>
        This flavorful chicken dish is perfect for summer grilling. The chicken
        breasts are seasoned with zesty lemon and spicy black pepper, then
        grilled to juicy perfection. Serve it alongside your favorite grilled
        vegetables for a healthy and delicious meal.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row recipe-instructions">
    <div class="col-md-4 ingredient-list">
      <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" class="ingredient" /> 4 boneless, skinless
          chicken breasts
        </li>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" class="ingredient" /> 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice
        </li>
        <li><input type="checkbox" class="ingredient" /> 1/4 cup olive oil</li>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" class="ingredient" /> 4 cloves garlic, minced
        </li>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" class="ingredient" /> 2 teaspoons freshly
          ground black pepper
        </li>
        <li><input type="checkbox" class="ingredient" /> 1 teaspoon salt</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-8 cooking-instruction">
      <h3>Instruction</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>
          In a small bowl, whisk together the olive oil, lemon juice, lemon
          zest, black pepper, salt, and garlic powder.
        </li>
        <li>
          Place the chicken breasts in a large resealable plastic bag, pour in
          the marinade, and seal the bag. Turn the bag to coat the chicken
          evenly. Marinate in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour, or up to 8
          hours.
        </li>
        <li>
          Preheat the grill to medium-high heat. Remove the chicken from the
          marinade and discard the marinade.
        </li>
        <li>
          Grill the chicken for 6 to 8 minutes per side, or until the internal
          temperature reaches 165°F (74°C). Allow the chicken to rest for 5
          minutes before slicing and serving.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="comment-section">
    <h3>Comments</h3>
    <div class="comment">
      <h5>Alex kagosi</h5>
      <p>
        Wow, this grilled chicken recipe was a hit with my family! The
        combination of zesty lemon and spicy black pepper was just perfect. We
        loved how juicy and flavorful the chicken turned out. Will definitely be
        making this again soon!
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="post-comment">
      <form method="post" action="/recipe">
